adium, and the host venue for the Closing Ceremony.\", \"from\": 402, \"to\": 596, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 426, \"end\": 431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999981216661, \"rank\": 1.878432985038341e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ourPrivacy notice\", \"from\": 407, \"to\": 424}, {\"ngram\": \"its thirdOlympicsthis summer\", \"from\": 437, \"to\": 465}, {\"ngram\": \"the Stade de France\", \"from\": 498, \"to\": 517}, {\"ngram\": \"the country's national stadium\", \"from\": 519, \"to\": 549}, {\"ngram\": \"the host\", \"from\": 555, \"to\": 563}, {\"ngram\": \"the Closing Ceremony\", \"from\": 574, \"to\": 594}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The stadium, which has recently hosted the Rugby World Cup final, the final of Euro 2016 and the Champions League final in 2022, is the largest stadium for athletics events in Europe, capable of holding over 77,000 fans.\", \"from\": 598, \"to\": 818, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 641, \"end\": 656, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rugby_World_Cup\", \"score\": 0.9973652382304209, \"rank\": 0.001982892423068263, \"text\": \"Rugby World Cup\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q10962\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rugby_World_Cup\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rugby_World_Cup\"}, {\"begin\": 695, \"end\": 711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA_Champions_League\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.039977488846536e-21, \"text\": \"Champions League\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA_Champions_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA_Champions_League\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The stadium\", \"from\": 598, \"to\": 609}, {\"ngram\": \"Euro\", \"from\": 677, \"to\": 681}, {\"ngram\": \"the largest stadium\", \"from\": 730, \"to\": 749}, {\"ngram\": \"athletics events\", \"from\": 754, \"to\": 770}, {\"ngram\": \"Europe\", \"from\": 774, \"to\": 780}, {\"ngram\": \"over 77,000 fans\", \"from\": 801, \"to\": 817}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The athletics track is usually hidden under the field for football and rugby matches, and ahead of the games a new track has been laid.\", \"from\": 820, \"to\": 955, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The athletics track\", \"from\": 820, \"to\": 839}, {\"ngram\": \"the field\", \"from\": 864, \"to\": 873}, {\"ngram\": \"football\", \"from\": 878, \"to\": 886}, {\"ngram\": \"rugby matches\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 904}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 919, \"to\": 928}, {\"ngram\": \"a new track\", \"from\": 929, \"to\": 940}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This new track, manufactured by Italian surface and equipment specialist Mondo, is an eye-catching shade of purple.\", \"from\": 957, \"to\": 1072, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 989, \"end\": 996, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.9798704492679855, \"rank\": 0.020060719222748935, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1030, \"end\": 1035, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondo_film\", \"score\": 0.5445157254396686, \"rank\": 0.5625168600856836, \"text\": \"Mondo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondo_film\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondo_film\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This new track\", \"from\": 957, \"to\": 971}, {\"ngram\": \"an eye-catching shade\", \"from\": 1040, \"to\": 1061}, {\"ngram\": \"purple\", \"from\": 1065, \"to\": 1071}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alain Blondel, sports manager in charge of athletics forParis 2024, explained that the track's colour is the simple result of a design approach.\", \"from\": 1074, \"to\": 1218, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1074, \"end\": 1087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alain_Blondel\", \"score\": 0.9999990810651654, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alain Blondel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alain_Blondel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alain_Blondel\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sports manager\", \"from\": 1089, \"to\": 1103}, {\"ngram\": \"charge\", \"from\": 1107, \"to\": 1113}, {\"ngram\": \"athletics\", \"from\": 1117, \"to\": 1126}, {\"ngram\": \"forParis\", \"from\": 1127, \"to\": 1135}, {\"ngram\": \"the track's colour\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1175}, {\"ngram\": \"the simple result\", \"from\": 1179, \"to\": 1196}, {\"ngram\": \"a design approach\", \"from\": 1200, \"to\": 1217}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said that the Organising Committee wanted \\\"to come up with a track that was different from what we had seen, to maintain the creative approach, [and] to go a little bit outside the box\\\".\", \"from\": 1220, \"to\": 1409, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Organising Committee\", \"from\": 1233, \"to\": 1257}, {\"ngram\": \"a track\", \"from\": 1282, \"to\": 1289}, {\"ngram\": \"the creative approach\", \"from\": 1344, \"to\": 1365}, {\"ngram\": \"the box\", \"from\": 1400, \"to\": 1407}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The look of the Games includes three colours for all the competition venues: blue, green and purple.\", \"from\": 1411, \"to\": 1512, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The look\", \"from\": 1412, \"to\": 1420}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1424, \"to\": 1433}, {\"ngram\": \"three colours\", \"from\": 1443, \"to\": 1456}, {\"ngram\": \"purple\", \"from\": 1505, \"to\": 1511}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We decided on this purple track with different tones: lighter for the track, darker for the service areas, and grey for the turns at the end of the bend, reminding of the ash-coloured tracks that were there 100 years ago for the Olympic Games [in] Paris [in] 1924.\\\"\", \"from\": 1513, \"to\": 1778, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1761, \"end\": 1766, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999981216661, \"rank\": 1.878432985038341e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this purple track\", \"from\": 1527, \"to\": 1544}, {\"ngram\": \"different tones\", \"from\": 1550, \"to\": 1565}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 1579, \"to\": 1588}, {\"ngram\": \"the service areas\", \"from\": 1601, \"to\": 1618}, {\"ngram\": \"the turns\", \"from\": 1633, \"to\": 1642}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 1646, \"to\": 1653}, {\"ngram\": \"the bend\", \"from\": 1657, \"to\": 1665}, {\"ngram\": \"the ash-coloured tracks\", \"from\": 1680, \"to\": 1703}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1738, \"to\": 1755}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to the Olympics website, purple has never been seen before on an athletics track, and Blondel emphasised that the Committee \\\"had to work hard on the colours, so that they came out in the best possible tones to highlight the athletes\\\".\", \"from\": 1780, \"to\": 2024, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics website\", \"from\": 1793, \"to\": 1813}, {\"ngram\": \"purple\", \"from\": 1815, \"to\": 1821}, {\"ngram\": \"an athletics track\", \"from\": 1852, \"to\": 1870}, {\"ngram\": \"Blondel\", \"from\": 1876, \"to\": 1883}, {\"ngram\": \"the Committee\", \"from\": 1900, \"to\": 1913}, {\"ngram\": \"the colours\", \"from\": 1935, \"to\": 1946}, {\"ngram\": \"the best possible tones\", \"from\": 1973, \"to\": 1996}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 2010, \"to\": 2022}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's a track, it has to be pretty, but above all it's a stage on which the athletes are going to perform.\", \"from\": 2026, \"to\": 2132, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a track\", \"from\": 2032, \"to\": 2039}, {\"ngram\": \"a stage\", \"from\": 2081, \"to\": 2088}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 2098, \"to\": 2110}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What's really important is that the colours and the athletes stand out.\\\"\", \"from\": 2133, \"to\": 2205, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the colours\", \"from\": 2165, \"to\": 2176}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 2181, \"to\": 2193}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Plenty more modifications are being made to the Stade de France, including the addition of two new screens - each the size of a tennis court - and the installation of 650 new lights.\", \"from\": 2207, \"to\": 2389, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Plenty more modifications\", \"from\": 2207, \"to\": 2232}, {\"ngram\": \"the Stade de France\", \"from\": 2251, \"to\": 2270}, {\"ngram\": \"the addition\", \"from\": 2282, \"to\": 2294}, {\"ngram\": \"two new screens\", \"from\": 2298, \"to\": 2313}, {\"ngram\": \"each the size\", \"from\": 2316, \"to\": 2329}, {\"ngram\": \"a tennis court\", \"from\": 2333, \"to\": 2347}, {\"ngram\": \"the installation\", \"from\": 2354, \"to\": 2370}, {\"ngram\": \"650 new lights\", \"from\": 2374, \"to\": 2388}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 2391, \"to\": 2621, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2442, \"end\": 2453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 0.9999999977253538, \"rank\": 1.5692193409209002e-09, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"thought-provoking conversations\", \"from\": 2396, \"to\": 2427}, {\"ngram\": \"their replies\